e/80678/why-does-grand-theft-auto-online-launch-two-weeks-after |archivedate=12 April 2014 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n<!-- Awards -->\n\n<ref name=\"bafta\">{{cite news |last=Cork |first=Jeff |title=Last Of Us, Tearaway, Grand Theft Auto V Win Big At The BAFTA Awards |url=http://www.gameinformer.com/b/news/archive/2014/03/13/last-of-us-tearaway-win-big-at-the-bafta-awards.aspx |work=[[Game Informer]] |date=13 March 2014 |accessdate=27 April 2014}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"GameTrailers\">{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TDu3Nz79BPc |title=Game of the Year Awards 2013 - Best Multiplayer Game |author=GameTrailers |work=[[YouTube]] |publisher=[[Google]] |date=9 January 2014 |accessdate=17 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Golden Joystick 19\">{{cite web |url=https://www.pcgamer.com/how-to-watch-the-golden-joystick-awards-2019/ |title=See the Golden Joystick Awards 2019 winners |last=Senior |first=Tom |work=[[PC Gamer]] |publisher=[[Gamer Network]] |date=15 November 2019 |accessdate=16 November 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191116011205/https://www.pcgamer.com/how-to-watch-the-golden-joystick-awards-2019/ |archivedate=16 November 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Golden Joystick 19 Nom\">{{cite web |url=http://www.pushsquare.com/news/2019/09/days_gone_rides_off_with_three_nominations_in_this_years_golden_joystick_awards |title=Days Gone Rides Off with Three Nominations in This Year's Golden Joystick Awards |last=Tailby |first=Stephen |work=Push Square |publisher=[[Gamer Network]] |date=September 20, 2019 |accessdate=November 16, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190920222955/http://www.pushsquare.com/news/2019/09/days_gone_rides_off_with_three_nominations_in_this_years_golden_joystick_awards |archivedate=September 20, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"GR-Disappoint\">{{cite web |url=http://www.gamerevolution.com/news/biggest-disappointment-2013-23131 |title=Biggest Disappointment 2013 |last=Tan |first=Nicholas |publisher=[[Game Revolution]]. Net Revolution |date=17 December 2013 |accessdate=8 January 2014}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"HG-Disappoint\">{{cite news |url=http://www.hardcoregamer.com/2013/12/21/2013-most-disappointing/67167/ |title=2013 Most Disappointing |work=Hardcore Gamer |date=21 December 2013 |accessdate=24 December 2013}}</ref>\n}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|http://www.rockstargames.com/GTAOnline/}}\n\n{{Grand Theft Auto}}\n{{Portal bar|Video games|border=yes}}\n\n[[Category:2013 video games]]\n[[Category:Grand Theft Auto]]\n[[Category:Grand Theft Auto V]]\n[[Category:Multiplayer online games]]\n[[Category:Multiplayer video games]]\n[[Category:Organized crime video games]]\n[[Category:Open world video games]]\n[[Category:Persistent worlds]]\n[[Category:PlayStation 3 games]]\n[[Category:PlayStation 4 games]]\n[[Category:Video games developed in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Video games set in the United States]]\n[[Category:Video games with user-generated gameplay content]]\n[[Category:Windows games]]\n[[Category:Xbox 360 games]]\n[[Category:Xbox One games]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Online multiplayer action-adventure game}}\n{{Use British English|date=July 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2018}}\n{{Infobox video game\n| title      = Grand Theft Auto Online\n| image      = Grand Theft Auto Online.jpg\n| developer  = [[Rockstar North]]\n| publisher  = [[Rockstar Games]]\n| director   = [[Leslie Benzies]]\n| producer   = Andy Duthie\n| designer   = Leslie Benzies\n| programmer = {{Unbulleted list|Adam Fowler|Daniel Yelland|Robert Trickey}}\n| artist     = Aaron Garbut\n| composer   = <!-- Blank because of Wikidata -->\n| series     = ''[[Grand Theft Auto]]''\n| engine     = [[Rockstar Advanced Game Engine|RAGE]]\n| platforms  = {{Unbulleted list|[[PlayStation 3]]|[[Xbox 360]]|[[PlayStation 4]]|[[Xbox One]]|[[Microsoft Windows]]}}\n| released   = {{Collapsible list|titlestyle=font-weight:normal;background:transparent;text-align:left;|title=1 October 2013|'''PlayStation 3''', '''Xbox 360'''|1 October 2013|'''PlayStation 4''', '''Xbox One'''|18 November 2014|'''Microsoft Windows'''|14 April 2015}}\n| genre      = [[Action-adventure]]\n| modes      = [[Multiplayer]]\n}}\n\n'''''Grand Theft Auto Online''''' is an [[Multiplayer video game|online multiplayer]] [[action-adventure game]] developed by [[Rockstar North]] and published by [[Rockstar Games]]. It was released on 1 October 2013 for [[PlayStation 3]] and [[Xbox 360]], and was released on 18 November 2014 for [[PlayStation 4]] and [[Xbox One]], with a [[Microsoft Windows]] version on 14 April 2015. The game is the online component of ''[[Grand Theft Auto V]]''. Set within the fictional state of San Andreas (based on [[Southern California]]), ''Grand Theft Auto Online'' allows up to 30 players{{efn|name=players}} to explore the [[open world]] and engage in [[Cooperative gameplay|cooperative]] or competitive game matches. The open-world design lets players [[Nonlinear gameplay|freely roam]] San Andreas, which includes open countryside and the fictional city of [[Los Santos (Grand Theft Auto)|Los Santos]] (based on Los Angeles).\n\nDeveloped in tandem with the single-player mode, ''Grand Theft Auto Online'' was conceived as a separate experience to be played in a continually evolving world. At launch, it suffered widespread technical issues resulting in the inability to play missions and loss of character data. It initially polarised reviewers, being criticized for its lack of direction and repetitive missions, with praise particularly directed at the scope and open-ended gameplay. It won divided [[List of accolades received by Grand Theft Auto V|year-end accolades]], ranging from Biggest Disappointment to Best Multiplayer, from several gaming publications. The game receives frequent free updates that further expand on the game modes and content, which has improved critical reception. The 2015 ''Heists'' update had been especially well-received by the critics.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2015/03/05/gta-5-online-heists-hands-on-theyre-real-and-theyre-spectacular |title=GTA 5 Online Heists Hands-On: They're Real And They're Spectacular |work=[[IGN]] |publisher=[[Ziff Davis]] |date=5 March 2015 |accessdate=25 November 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Gameplay ==\nDeveloped in tandem with ''Grand Theft Auto V'', ''Grand Theft Auto Online'' was conceived as a separate experience to be played in a continually evolving world.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.computerandvideogames.com/423020/gta-v-interview-rockstar-north-president-leslie-benzies-on-gta-online/ |title=Interview: Rockstar North president Leslie Benzies on GTA Online and GTA V |last=Weaver |first=Tim |work=[[Computer and Video Games]] |publisher=[[Future plc]] |date=16 August 2013 |accessdate=17 August 2013}}</ref> Up to 30 players{{efn|name=players|The PlayStation 3 and Xbox 360 versions of ''Grand Theft Auto Online'' allow up to 16 concurrent players,<ref name=\"Persistent\"/> while the PlayStation 4, Xbox One, and PC versions allow up to 30 concurrent players.<ref name=\"ReReleaseDate\">{{cite web |url=http://www.rockstargames.com/newswire/article/52308/grand-theft-auto-v-release-dates-and-exclusive-content |title=Grand Theft Auto V Release Dates and Exclusive Content Details for PlayStation 4, Xbox One and PC |author=R* Q |work=Rockstar Newswire |publisher=[[Rockstar Games]] |date=12 September 2014 |accessdate=12 September 2014}}</ref>}} freely roam across a re-creation of the single-player world and enter lobbies to complete jobs (story-driven competitive and cooperative modes).<ref name=\"Persistent\">{{cite web |url=http://www.computerandvideogames.com/424264/gta-online-first-look-rockstars-persistent-online-world-is-its-most-ambitious-project-in-years/ |title=GTA Online first look: Rockstar's persistent online world is its most ambitious project in years |last=Dawkins |first=Daniel |work=[[Computer and Video Games]] |publisher=[[Future plc]] |date=15 August 2013 |accessdate=16 August 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130817062416/http://www.computerandvideogames.com/424264/gta-online-first-look-rockstars-persistent-online-world-is-its-most-ambitious-project-in-years/ |archivedate=17 August 2013}}</ref> The Content Creator toolset lets players create their own parameters for custom jobs, like racetracks and [[deathmatch]] weapon [[Spawning (video gaming)|spawn points]].<ref name=\"CVG-online\">{{cite web |url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/why-grand-theft-auto-online-is-crazy-enough-to-work/1100-6412714/ |title=Why Grand Theft Auto Online is Crazy Enough to Work |work=[[GameSpot]] |publisher=[[CBS Interactive]] |last=McInnis |first=Shaun |date=16 August 2013 |accessdate=16 August 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131018003853/http://www.gamespot.com/articles/why-grand-theft-auto-online-is-crazy-enough-to-work/1100-6412714/ |archivedate=18 October 2013 |url-status=live}}</ref> Players may band together in organised player teams called crews to complete jobs together. [[Rockstar Games Social Club]] extends crews formed in ''[[Max Payne 3]]''{{'s}} multiplayer mode to that of ''Grand Theft Auto Online''. Players can create their own crews and join up to five total. Crews win multiplayer matches to earn [[experience point]]s and climb [[online leaderboards]].<ref name=\"krupa1\">{{cite web |url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2012/03/22/max-payne-3-rockstars-multiplayer-reinvention |title=Max Payne 3: Rockstar's Multiplayer Reinvention |last=Krupa |first=Daniel |work=[[IGN]] |publisher=[[Ziff Davis]] |date=22 March 2012 |accessdate=28 March 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120825145735/http://www.ign.com/articles/2012/03/22/max-payne-3-rockstars-multiplayer-reinvention |archivedate=25 August 2012 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn ''Grand Theft Auto Online'', players create a new character specific to the online world, which shows on the screen's Switch Wheel alongside single-player characters Franklin, Michael, and Trevor.<ref name=\"Shacknews: weeks after\"/> The [[player-character]]s are designed by a genetics-related process.<ref name=\"IGN review\"/> Greater control is given to the character's clothes and hairstyles. The protagonist arrives in [[Los Santos (Grand Theft Auto)|Los Santos]] by plane and is picked up by Lamar Davis, who gives the character a gun and a car. An hour-long tutorial introduces the player to the various game modes, driving, fighting, and game progression mechanics.<ref name=\"IGN review\"/> The story is not central in the multiplayer, though it serves as a prequel to the single-player story, where characters from the single-player are woven in.<ref name=\"IGN review\"/>\n\nSimilar to single-player, players can level up their character's attributes such as driving and stamina. Exclusive to ''GTA Online'' is a system of earning experience, usually by successful completion of activities. Accumulating enough experience to level up unlocks weapons, clothing, car customisations, and more advanced activities (such as parachuting and aircraft). Once unlocked, items need to be purchased with in-game currency, which can be earned or purchased with real money. Players can circumvent an activity's level requirements by joining a game with others of a sufficient rank. There are options to play alone or with friends, and an option for \"Passive Mode\", which makes the player immune to other players.<ref name=\"IGN review\"/>\n\nAside from the open world, there are three main types of set activities: racing (by car, bike, air or boat), Deathmatch (team or free-for-all), and objective-based Contact Missions (simplified single-player-like storyline jobs, usually cooperative). ''Online'' uses lock-on aim and emphasises stealth in firefights. \"Adversary Mode\" adds several asymmetric variations on these activities, including \"Siege Mentality\" where one team is besieged by another, and \"Hasta La Vista\" where truckers chase down cyclists (reminiscent of the truck/motorcycle chase in ''[[Terminator 2: Judgment Day]]''). \"Survival\" pits a team of up to four players against ten waves of enemies, similar to the Zombies mode in ''[[Call of Duty: Black Ops]]''. The Heists Update released on 10 March 2015 adds five [[Cooperative gameplay|co-op]] elaborate multi-part missions, each mission having several setup jobs leading up to the finale crime which is a high-profit job. The player who is the heist leader has to unlock each heist in order and pay the upfront costs, while receiving the largest payoff (at the end, if successfully completed) and getting their progress saved, while other players (the crew members) can join any setup/finale jobs without prerequisite and get paid a cut for each mission passed. The heists, all requiring four players except the first which is two-player, often assign specific roles to players such as driver, gunner, etc. and/or may split them apart, and a headset is recommended for communicating with other players.<ref name=\"martin1\">{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.com/gaming/grand-theft-auto/review/a636845/gta-online-re-review-18-months-on-open-world-multiplayer-lives-up-to-its-potential/ |title=GTA Online re-review: 18 months on, open-world multiplayer lives up to its potential |last=Martin |first=Liam |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Corporation]] |date=30 April 2015 |accessdate=29 March 2016 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6gMATGHQY?url=http://www.digitalspy.com/gaming/grand-theft-auto/review/a636845/gta-online-re-review-18-months-on-open-world-multiplayer-lives-up-to-its-potential/ |archivedate=28 March 2016 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"mccaffrey2\">{{cite web |url=http://ign.com/articles/2015/03/05/gta-5-online-heists-hands-on-theyre-real-and-theyre-spectacular?page=2 |title=GTA 5 Online Heists Hand-On: They're Real and They're Spectacular |last=McCaffrey |first=Ryan |work=[[IGN]] |publisher=[[Ziff Davis]] |date=5 March 2015 |accessdate=29 March 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150306074952/http://www.ign.com/articles/2015/03/05/gta-5-online-heists-hands-on-theyre-real-and-theyre-spectacular?page=2 |archivedate=6 March 2015 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe game includes a content creation tool that lets players make automobile races and [[deathmatch]]es.<ref name=\"Shacknews: weeks after\"/> Players can choose the location, start and spawn points, and weapon and vehicle drops in deathmatches, and the location, route, race type, and player count in air, land, or sea races. Creations have to be tested against [[Artificial intelligence (video games)|computer-controlled]] players before the mode is available online. The creations can also be published for others to use. Rockstar tags what they deem to be the best as \"Rockstar Verified\".<ref name=\"IGN: deathmatch\"/>\n\n== Development ==\n''Grand Theft Auto Online'' launched on 1 October 2013, two weeks after the release of ''Grand Theft Auto V''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2013/10/01/when-can-we-start-playing-gta-online |title=When Can We Start Playing GTA Online |last=Dyer |first=Mitch |work=[[IGN]] |publisher=[[Ziff Davis]] |date=30 September 2013 |accessdate=1 October 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131001002859/http://www.ign.com/articles/2013/10/01/when-can-we-start-playing-gta-online |archivedate=1 October 2013 |url-status=live}}</ref> Many players reported that they had difficulties connecting to the game's servers and the Social Club web service, and others further reported that the game would freeze while loading early missions.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2013/10/04/gta-online-launch-issues-rockstar-speaks |title=GTA Online Launch Issues&nbsp;\u2013 Rockstar Speaks |last=Karmali |first=Luke |work=[[IGN]] |publisher=[[Ziff Davis]] |date=4 October 2013 |accessdate=8 October 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131005074936/http://www.ign.com/articles/2013/10/04/gta-online-launch-issues-rockstar-speaks |archivedate=5 October 2013 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.polygon.com/2013/10/1/4790494/gta-online-grand-theft-auto-5-server-issues |title=GTA Online now live, Rockstar looking into server issues (update) |last=Sarkar |first=Samit |work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |publisher=[[Vox Media]] |date=1 October 2013 |accessdate=8 October 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131001135409/http://www.polygon.com/2013/10/1/4790494/gta-online-grand-theft-auto-5-server-issues |archivedate=1 October 2013 |url-status=live}}</ref> Rockstar released a technical patch on 5 October in an effort to resolve the issues.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.polygon.com/2013/10/6/4809270/gta-online-connection-issues-resolved-lost-items-still-being |title=GTA Online connection issues resolved, lost items still being investigated |last=Farokhmanesh |first=Megan |work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |publisher=[[Vox Media]] |date=6 October 2013 |accessdate=8 October 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131006180426/http://www.polygon.com/2013/10/6/4809270/gta-online-connection-issues-resolved-lost-items-still-being |archivedate=6 October 2013 |url-status=live}}</ref> The [[Micropayment|microtransaction]] system, which allows players to purchase game content using real money, was also suspended as a fail-safe.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2013/oct/04/gta-v-online-ps3-fix-xbox-360 |title=GTA V Online: Rockstar launches update to fix PS3 problems |last=Stuart |first=Keith |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |date=4 October 2013 |accessdate=8 October 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131004121138/http://www.theguardian.com/technology/2013/oct/04/gta-v-online-ps3-fix-xbox-360 |archivedate=4 October 2013 |url-status=live}}</ref> Problems persisted the second week following launch, and some players reported their player-character progress as having disappeared.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.videogamer.com/ps3/gta5/news/gta_online_rockstar_investigating_missing_characters_progress_and_money.html |title=GTA Online: Rockstar investigating missing characters, progress and money |last=Scammell |first=David |work=VideoGamer.com |publisher=Pro-G Media |date=7 October 2013 |accessdate=8 October 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131014095137/http://www.videogamer.com/ps3/gta5/news/gta_online_rockstar_investigating_missing_characters_progress_and_money.html |archivedate=14 October 2013 |url-status=live}}</ref> Another technical patch was released on 10 October combating the issues, and players experiencing issues were told not to recreate their multiplayer avatars.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2013/10/10/gta-online-deleted-character-fix-released-by-rockstar |title=GTA Online Deleted Character Fix Released by Rockstar |last=Karmali |first=Luke |work=[[IGN]] |publisher=[[Ziff Davis]] |date=10 October 2013 |accessdate=13 October 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131010094338/http://www.ign.com/articles/2013/10/10/gta-online-deleted-character-fix-released-by-rockstar |archivedate=10 October 2013 |url-status=live}}</ref> As recompense for the technical issues, Rockstar offered a stimulus of GTA $500,000 (in-game currency) to the accounts of all players connected to ''Online'' since launch.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2013-11-07-gta-onlines-stimulus-package-is-live |title=GTA Online's stimulus package is live |last=Matulef |first=Jeffrey |work=[[Eurogamer]] |publisher=Gamer Network |date=7 November 2013 |accessdate=17 March 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131107115626/http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2013-11-07-gta-onlines-stimulus-package-is-live |archivedate=7 November 2013 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[Take-Two Interactive]], Rockstar's parent company, stated that by February 2014, 70 percent of players with Internet access had played ''Grand Theft Auto Online'', and that the game's microtransactions system was the largest contributor to the company's digital revenue since the launch of ''Grand Theft Auto Online''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mcvuk.com/news/read/70-of-gta-v-gamers-have-played-gta-online/0127604 |title=70% of GTA V gamers have played GTA Online |last=Dring |first=Christopher |work=[[MCV (magazine)|MCV]] |publisher=Intent Media |date=3 February 2014 |accessdate=16 March 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140207111302/http://www.mcvuk.com/news/read/70-of-gta-v-gamers-have-played-gta-online/0127604 |archivedate=7 February 2014 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2013, Rockstar announced that they planned to release [[downloadable content]] in 2014 that expands the single-player mode and creates new story for the lead characters,<ref name=\"Deathmatch Race1\"/> however no single-player expansions have been released.<ref name=\"Forbes\"/> It has been reported since then that ''The Doomsday Heist'' DLC update, released in December 2017, was initially intended to be released for the single-player mode before refocusing it for the online mode.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://comicbook.com/gaming/2017/12/17/grand-theft-auto-online-single-player-dlc-v/ |title=Report: Grand Theft Auto Online\u2019s Doomsday Heist May Have Originally Been Single Player DLC |last=Workman |first=Robert |work=ComicBook.com |publisher=comicbook/wgg |date=17 December 2017 |accessdate=17 January 2019}}</ref> Rockstar announced in September 2015 that the PlayStation 3 and Xbox 360 versions of the online mode will no longer receive any new additional content, due to limitation in the console capacity.<ref name=\"7th Gen\"/> This was criticised by ''[[Forbes]]'' writer Paul Tassi, who felt that Rockstar was \"cutting out a lot of potential customers\" who continued to play on the older systems, adding that the re-releases on PlayStation 4 and Xbox One were lacking in additional content.<ref name=\"Forbes\"/>\n\n== Additional content ==\n<!-- The detail in this section needs to be reviewed to make sure it doesn't fall foul of item 4 of WP:NOTCHANGELOG -->\n\nPost-release content is continually added to ''Grand Theft Auto Online'' and the single-player mode of ''Grand Theft Auto V'' through free title updates.\n\n===2013===\nThe ''Beach Bum'' update, released on 19 November 2013, added more beach-themed jobs and customisation content for players.<ref name=\"Beach Bum\"/> In December, Rockstar announced that they planned to release [[downloadable content]] in 2014 that expands the single-player mode and creates new story for the lead characters;<ref name=\"Deathmatch Race1\"/> but no further announcements have been made.<ref name=\"Forbes\"/> The ''Deathmatch & Race Creators'' update was released on 11 December and lets players create their own deathmatches and races.<ref name=\"Deathmatch Race2\"/> The ''Capture Update'' was released on 17 December and adds a new team-based [[capture the flag]] mode called Capture.<ref name=\"Capture\"/> On 24 December, the ''Holiday Gifts'' update added [[Christmas]]-themed items to the online mode. It also gave players discounts on in-game vehicles, weapons, apartments and other items. The items and discounts were available until 5 January 2014. The update also added snowfall to the game world during Christmas.<ref name=\"Holiday Gifts\"/>\n\n===2014===\nCoinciding with the 2014 [[Valentine's Day]], the ''Valentine's Day Massacre Special'' update released on 13 February added [[Bonnie and Clyde]]-themed content to the game for a limited time until the end of February.<ref name=\"Valentine\"/> ''The Business Update'', released on 4 March, added multiple business-themed items to the game.<ref name=\"Business\"/> On 11 April, the ''Capture Creator Update'' was released that added the ability for players to create their own Capture jobs using the Content Creator.<ref name=\"Creator\"/> ''The High Life Update'' released on 13 May added a few new contact missions, new vehicles, clothes and weapons. It also added new apartments, the ability to purchase two properties at any one time and the Mental State gameplay statistic that monitors player behaviour in-game.<ref name=\"High Life\"/> The ''I'm Not a Hipster Update'' was released on 17 June and added [[Hipster (contemporary subculture)|hipster]]-themed customisation items, and retro-themed vehicles and weapons.<ref name=\"Hipster\"/><ref name=\"Hipster IGN\"/> The ''Independence Day Special'' update was released on 1 July to celebrate the [[Independence Day (United States)|U.S. Independence Day]] and added patriotic-themed vehicles, weapons and customisation items for a limited time. The patch added new properties to ''Grand Theft Auto Online'' and the \"On Call Matchmaking\" feature that lets player accept a job invite and keep playing until the lobby is full.<ref name=\"Independence\"/> The ''San Andreas Flight School'' update, released on 19 August 2014, added new features and vehicles related to the in-game flying school.<ref name=\"Flight\"/> The ''Last Team Standing'' update was released on 2 October 2014. It added 10 new jobs for, new motorcycles, weapons and creator support for the Last Team Standing mode.<ref name=\"LTS\"/> On 18 December 2014, the ''Festive Surprise'' update was released, which added two new weapons, four holiday-themed vehicles and Christmas-themed apparel that was announced to be available until 5 January 2015. The update also added the ability to buy a third property.<ref name=\"Festive\"/>\n\n===2015===\nThe ''Online Heists'' update was a highly anticipated feature of ''Grand Theft Auto Online''.<ref name=\"highly\"/><ref name=\"anticipated\"/> After numerous delays,<ref name=\"Heist Delay\"/><ref name=\"Heist Delay2\"/> the update launched on 10 March 2015, suffering some initial technical difficulties due to the increased user load.<ref name=\"Heist Launch\"/> ''Ill-Gotten Gains Part 1'', released on 10 June 2015, added additional vehicles, clothing items and weapon decals. Some gameplay features were also affected, such as a redesign of the in-game car websites, the addition of a first-person vehicle hood camera in the PlayStation 4 and Xbox One versions, and the ability to cycle through targets when using lock-on missiles, among other minor changes.<ref name=\"Ill 1\"/> ''Ill-Gotten Gains Part 2'', released on 8 July 2015, added vehicles and weapons. It also added the radio station ''The Lab'', previously exclusive to the Windows version of the game, to all other versions. This was also the final update for both the Xbox 360 and the PlayStation 3, citing hardware limitations.<ref name=\"Ill 2\"/> The ''Freemode Events'' update launched on 15 September 2015, added new modes and activities. It also added the Xbox One and PlayStation 4 for ''Rockstar Editor'' and ''Director Mode'', previously exclusive to the Windows version of the game, It was added a new lobbies.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rockstargames.com/newswire/article/52499/gta-online-freemode-events-update-now-available-for-ps4 |title=GTA Online: Freemode Events Update Now Available for PS4, Xbox One & PC |website=Rockstar Games |accessdate=2015-09-17}}</ref> ''Lowriders'', released on 10 October 2015, added a new set of missions, hosted by Lamar, additional vehicles, available vehicle upgrades, weapons, clothing items and Benny's Original Motor Works vehicle shop. The update gave players the ability to obtain and customise [[Lowrider]]s, including upgrades such as interior customisation, hydraulics, and decals. The update also introduced the [[machete]] and machine-pistol weapons.<ref name=\"Lowriders\"/> ''Halloween Surprise'', released on 29 October 2015 for a limited time, featured two new Halloween-themed vehicles, [[flashlight]] and additional masks and ornaments, along with slasher-themed Adversary Modes. They were available until 16 November 2015.<ref name=\"Halloween\"/> The ''Executives and Other Criminals'' update released on 15 December 2015. It was new features customizable Penthouse Apartments and new vehicles. It was added a new Extraction modes.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rockstargames.com/newswire/article/52545/gta-online-executives-and-other-criminals-now-available |title=GTA Online: Executives And Other Criminals Now Available |website=Rockstar Games |accessdate=2015-12-17}}</ref> The ''Festive Surprise'' update returned on 21 December 2015. In addition to the items available in the previous iteration, the new iteration added new festive themed clothes, fifteen new masks and a new car. The update also added a new Adversary mode on 23 December 2015.<ref name=\"Festive 2015\"/>\n\n===2016===\nAn update released on 28 January 2016 added a new Adversary mode called ''Drop Zone'' along with two new sports cars.<ref name=\"Drop Zone\"/> ''Be My Valentine'' update launched on 10 February. The update included new outfits and cars as well as the content of the previous Valentine's Day themed-update. A couple-themed adversary mode was added by the update.<ref name=\"Valentine 2016\"/>\nThe ''Lowriders: Custom Classics'' update, released on 15 March, added three cars available for customisation along with new weapons, clothes and an Adversary mode called \"Sumo\".<ref name=\"Lowriders Custom Classics\"/> ''Further Adventures in Finance and Felony'' was released on 7 June. The update allows the player character to buy executive offices, hire criminal associates and become CEO of a criminal organisation which allows the player to participate in new jobs, challenges and purchase cargo warehouses. In addition the update adds new weapons, vehicles, attire, weapon attachments and a new Adversary mode called \"Trading Places.<ref name=\"Finance Felony\"/> The ''Cunning Stunts'' update released on 12 July added 13 new vehicles and 16 stunt races.<ref name=\"Cunning Stunts\"/> On 4 October, the ''Bikers'' update was launched, which introduced the ability to form motorcycle clubs, and clubhouses can be purchased at several new locations in San Andreas. The update also introduced new bikes, new weapons, new tattoos, new clothes, new businesses, and a new adversary mode.<ref name=\"Bikers\"/> Another update released in 8 November 2016, ''Deadline'', added a new adversary game mode based on the [[Tron (franchise)#Light cycles|light cycle]] races from [[Walt Disney Pictures|Disney]]'s ''[[Tron (franchise)|Tron]]'' film franchise, specifically those seen in the 2010 film, ''[[Tron: Legacy]]''.<ref name=\"Deadline\"/> 13 December 2016 saw the release of ''Import/Export''<ref name=\"Import Export\"/> as well as ''Festive Surprise 2016'' which brought an expansion to the ''Finance and Felony'' update as well as festive holiday content for a limited time to Grand Theft Auto Online, respectively.<ref name=\"Festive Surprise 2016\"/><ref name=\"Festive Surprise 2016 2\"/>\n\n===2017===\nThe ''Cunning Stunts: Special Vehicle Circuit'' released on 14 March 2017. Introduced special vehicle stunt Races and 20 new races.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.rockstargames.com/newswire/article/60158/Cunning-Stunts-Special-Vehicle-Circuit-Now-Available-New-Progen-GP1-an |title=GTA Online: Cunning Stunts: Special Vehicle Circuit - Now Available, New Progen GP1 & More |website=Rockstar Games |language=en-US |access-date=2017-03-16}}</ref> The ''Gunrunning'' update was released on 13 June 2017. It allows players to purchase [[Bunker|underground bunkers]] and turn them into illegal weaponry research, storage and production facilities, and allows players to own a customisable Mobile Operations Center (MOC), which unlocks missions that unlock discounted prices for vehicles related to the update, such as [[armoured personnel carrier]]s and armed off-road vehicles. It also allows players to customise their arsenal of weaponry, allowing unique and personal gun designs.<ref name=\"Gunrunning\"/> On 29 August, Rockstar released the ''Smuggler's Run'' update, which allows players to participate in the [[smuggling]] business. It also allows players to purchase new large [[Hangar|aircraft hangars]] and purchase a wide variety of aircraft with the addition of a new Adversary Mode job.<ref name=\"Smuggler's Run\"/> On 12 December 2017, Rockstar released the ''Doomsday Heist Update'', adding new heists with the possibility to play them in a group of 2-4 players.<ref name=\"Doomsday Heist\"/> A large extent of military-grade vehicles and new properties were also added. In late 2017, ''Festive Surprise'' allowed players to purchase [[Christmas]] and holiday-themed items.<ref name=\"Festive Surprise 2017\"/>\n\n===2018===\nReleased on 20 March 2018, the ''Southern San Andreas Super Sport Series'' introduced new races and modes to the game.<ref name=\"SSASSS\"/> The ''After Hours'' update released on 24 July, featuring a new nightlife business. The update features the return of \"Gay\" Tony Prince from ''[[Grand Theft Auto: The Ballad of Gay Tony]]'', who serves as the co-owner of the nightclub. The new update features a variety of new vehicles and real life [[disc jockey|DJ]]s [[Solomun]], [[Tale Of Us (DJs)|Tale Of Us]], [[Dixon (DJ)|Dixon]] and [[The Black Madonna]].<ref name=\"After Hours\"/> The ''Arena War'' update was released on 11 December 2018 introduced new races and death races in Maze Bank Arena.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2018/12/12/gta-onlines-arena-war-blends-mad-max-and-robot-wars/ |title=GTA Online\u2019s Arena War blends Mad Max and Robot Wars |website=Rock Paper Shotgun |language=en-US |access-date=2018-12-25}}</ref>\n\n===2019===\n\nThe ''Diamond Casino & Resort'' update was released on 23 July 2019. The update introduced gambling, new automobiles and resort activities.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.rockstargames.com/newswire/article/61051/Grand-Opening-The-Diamond-Casino-Resort-is-Now-Open |title=Grand Opening: The Diamond Casino & Resort is Now Open |website=Rockstar Games |language=en-US |access-date=2019-07-25}}</ref> The in-game gambling activities are not available in certain regions, including a few US states, due to differing [[Gambling laws|laws and regulations]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.pcgamer.com/grand-theft-auto-onlines-new-casino-update-in-inaccessible-to-more-than-50-countries/ |title=GTA Online's new casino update is inaccessible to more than 50 countries |website=PC Gamer |language=en-US |access-date=2019-07-27}}</ref>\n\n''The Diamond Casino Heist'' update was released on 12 December 2019. It added a new heist which allowed players to choose between three different approaches and with more interactive mission design. Additionally, a new in-game radio station was added, curated by [[Skepta]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.rockstargames.com/newswire/article/61273/The-Diamond-Casino-Heist-Now-Available |title=The Diamond Casino Heist Now Available |website=Rockstar Games}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2019-12-20-the-diamond-casino-heist-is-gta-onlines-most-exhilarating-score-and-an-exercise-in-self-parody |title=The Diamond Casino Heist is GTA Online's most exhilarating score and an exercise in self-parody |first=Jordan |last=Oloman |date=20 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\n{{Video game reviews\n<!-- Aggregators -->\n| MC = (PS3) 83/100<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation-3/grand-theft-auto-online |title=Grand Theft Auto Online for PlayStation 3 Reviews |work=[[Metacritic]] |publisher=[[CBS Interactive]] |accessdate=15 March 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131005234729/http://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation-3/grand-theft-auto-online |archivedate=5 October 2013 |url-status=live}}</ref><br />(X360) 80/100<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/xbox-360/grand-theft-auto-online |title=Grand Theft Auto Online for Xbox 360 Reviews |work=[[Metacritic]] |publisher=[[CBS Interactive]] |accessdate=15 March 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131005174259/http://www.metacritic.com/game/xbox-360/grand-theft-auto-online |archivedate=5 October 2013 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n<!-- Reviewers -->\n| Destruct = 7/10<ref name=\"Destructoid GTA Online\">{{cite web |url=http://www.destructoid.com/review-grand-theft-auto-online-262832.phtml |title=Review: Grand Theft Auto Online |last=Carter |first=Chris |work=[[Destructoid]] |publisher=[[ModernMethod]] |date=8 October 2013 |accessdate=15 March 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131011093937/http://www.destructoid.com/review-grand-theft-auto-online-262832.phtml |archivedate=11 October 2013 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n| GSpot = 6/10{{efn|Carolyn Petit of GameSpot originally gave the game a score of 7/10 in her review from 11 October 2013,<ref name=\"GameSpot GTA Online\"/> but changed the score to 6/10 in her updated review from 5 May 2014.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gamespot.com/reviews/grand-theft-auto-online-updated-review/1900-6415752/ |title=Grand Theft Auto Online Updated Review |last=Petit |first=Carolyn |work=[[GameSpot]] |publisher=[[CBS Interactive]] |date=5 May 2014 |accessdate=12 May 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141017110602/http://www.gamespot.com/reviews/grand-theft-auto-online-updated-review/1900-6415752/ |archivedate=17 October 2014 |url-status=live}}</ref>}}\n| VG = 9/10<ref name=\"VideoGamer GTA Online\">{{cite web |url=http://www.videogamer.com/reviews/gta_online_review.html |title=GTA Online Review |last=Denton |first=Jon |work=VideoGamer.com |publisher=Pro-G Media |date=25 October 2013 |accessdate=15 March 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131030020920/http://www.videogamer.com/reviews/gta_online_review.html |archivedate=30 October 2013 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n| rev1 = ''[[Digital Spy]]''\n| rev1Score = {{Rating|3|5}}<ref name=\"Digital Spy GTA Online\">{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.com.au/gaming/review/a524019/gta-online-review-xbox-360-full-of-untapped-potential.html |title='GTA Online' review (Xbox 360): Full of untapped potential |last=Martin |first=Liam |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Corporation]] |date=17 October 2013 |accessdate=15 March 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140315184424/http://www.digitalspy.com.au/gaming/review/a524019/gta-online-review-xbox-360-full-of-untapped-potential.html |archivedate=15 March 2014 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n}}\n\n''Grand Theft Auto Online'' suffered widespread technical issues at launch, which prompted many reviewers to bemoan their experience with the game.<ref name=\"GameSpot GTA Online\">{{cite web |url=http://www.gamespot.com/reviews/grand-theft-auto-online-review/1900-6415473/ |title=Grand Theft Auto Online Review |last=Petit |first=Carolyn |work=[[GameSpot]] |publisher=[[CBS Interactive]] |date=11 October 2013 |accessdate=15 March 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131014030849/http://www.gamespot.com/reviews/grand-theft-auto-online-review/1900-6415473/ |archivedate=14 October 2013 |url-status=live}}</ref> Chris Carter of Destructoid criticised the \"messy launch\" and felt that Rockstar Games should have delayed it.<ref name=\"Destructoid GTA Online\"/> IGN's MacDonald considered her initial play sessions in ''Grand Theft Auto Online'' \"disastrous\",<ref name=\"IGN GTA Online\">{{cite web |url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2013/10/22/grand-theft-auto-online-review |title=Grand Theft Auto Online Review |last=MacDonald |first=Keza |work=[[IGN]] |publisher=[[Ziff Davis]] |date=22 October 2013 |accessdate=15 March 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131022085158/http://www.ign.com/articles/2013/10/22/grand-theft-auto-online-review |archivedate=22 October 2013 |url-status=live}}</ref> and Liam Martin of ''[[Digital Spy]]'' reported glitches including loss of his character data. While generally praising the scope of the experience, he considered ''Grand Theft Auto Online'' underwhelming as beholden to pre-launch anticipation let down by its technical issues.<ref name=\"Digital Spy GTA Online\"/> However, reviewers generally recognised the open-ended exploration and dynamic content as the strength of ''Grand Theft Auto Online''.<ref name=\"GameSpot GTA Online\"/><ref name=\"Digital Spy GTA Online\"/><ref name=\"IGN GTA Online\"/> Jon Denton of VideoGamer.com was particularly enthusiastic, and wrote that the \"endlessness\" of the gameplay made up for the technical issues.<ref name=\"VideoGamer GTA Online\"/>\n\nWhen ''Grand Theft Auto V'' was re-released for PlayStation 4 and Xbox One, ''Grand Theft Auto Online'' received similar critical reactions. IGN's Dan Stapleton reported low player counts in matches, long wait times in lobbies, server disconnection and occasional crashes. \"Because of that,\" he wrote, \"I can't strongly recommend ... the multiplayer experience alone\".<ref name=\"IGN Review 2\">{{cite web |url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2014/11/17/gta-5-playstation-4-and-xbox-one-review |title=GTA 5 PlayStation 4 and Xbox One Review |last=Stapleton |first=Dan |date=17 November 2014 |work=[[IGN]] |publisher=[[Ziff Davis]] |accessdate=23 November 2014 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6UISodAuq?url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2014/11/17/gta-5-playstation-4-and-xbox-one-review |archivedate=23 November 2014 |url-status=live}}</ref> VideoGamer.com found online character progression streamlined by comparison with the original version. According to them, the \"grind of just doing [[Player versus player|PvP]] until co-op Jobs arrive with regularity\"<ref name=\"VG PS4 Review\">{{cite web |url=http://www.videogamer.com/reviews/gta_5_review_ps4.html |title=Grand Theft Auto 5 Review |work=VideoGamer.com |publisher=Pro-G Media |date=20 November 2014 |accessdate=23 November 2014 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6UIT91nLm?url=http://www.videogamer.com/reviews/gta_5_review_ps4.html |archivedate=23 November 2014 |url-status=dead}}</ref> was lost, and newcomers would likely find multiplayer enjoyable and balanced. However, they wrote of frequent server disconnection, especially during load screens.<ref name=\"VG PS4 Review\"/> ''Game Informer''{{'}}s Reiner reported \"minimal lag or issues in the expanded firefights and races\".<ref name=\"Game Informer Review 2\">{{cite web |url=http://www.gameinformer.com/games/grand_theft_auto_v/b/playstation4/archive/2014/11/21/intimate-violence.aspx |title=Grand Theft Auto V&nbsp;\u2013 Intimate Violence |last=Reiner |first=Andrew |work=[[Game Informer]] |publisher=GameStop |date=21 November 2014 |accessdate=23 November 2014 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6UITxbiR2?url=http://www.gameinformer.com/games/grand_theft_auto_v/b/playstation4/archive/2014/11/21/intimate-violence.aspx |archivedate=23 November 2014 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nBesides technical issues, other aspects of ''Grand Theft Auto Online'' also received criticism. The character creation system was panned as unintuitive, who felt that the system only produced unattractive avatars.<ref name=\"Destructoid GTA Online\"/><ref name=\"Digital Spy GTA Online\"/><ref name=\"IGN GTA Online\"/> MacDonald of IGN noted an \"addictive rhythm\" to character progression and was enthusiastic about some of the job missions, although most eventually became monotonous.<ref name=\"IGN GTA Online\"/> GameSpot's Petit agreed with MacDonald, writing that \"early on, your mission options are dominated by bland [[Last man standing (gaming)|last team standing]] [[deathmatch]]es\".<ref name=\"GameSpot GTA Online\"/> ''Eurogamer's'' Rich Stanton said that the Contact Missions \"tend to work like this: four of you clump up in one or two cars, drive somewhere, spill out and shoot people, drive away\", while lacking a required [[Cooperative gameplay|co-op]] aspect such that some were possible to complete solo albeit with some difficulty.<ref name=\"eurogamer1\">{{cite web |last=Stanton |first=Rich |url=https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2015-03-11-have-gtas-heists-been-worth-the-wait |title=Have GTA's Heists been worth the wait? |publisher=Eurogamer.net |date=11 March 2015 |accessdate=21 September 2016}}</ref> GameSpot's Mark Walton wrote that the online mode \"suffers from a lack of direction\" for its open-ended and frenetic gameplay, in contrast to the single-player story, encouraging player behaviour where \"you end up seeing any nearby players as threats and pull out your weapon, ready to gun them down before they gun you down\", which created a distracting \"unending cycle of pointless slaughter\". Walton also noted that the game's reputation system was a weak deterrent against foul play; for instance you would go unpunished for killing another player as long as their vehicle wasn't destroyed. In addition, purchasing vehicles and weapons in-game was prohibitively expensive (especially compared to the single-player mode), which was further exacerbated by low mission payouts, with some suggesting that Rockstar Games was pushing online players towards using real money to [[Microtransaction|buy in-game currency]].<ref name=\"GameSpot Review 2\">{{cite web |url=http://www.gamespot.com/reviews/grand-theft-auto-5-ps4-xbox-one-review/1900-6415959/ |title=Grand Theft Auto V Review |last=Walton |first=Mark |work=[[GameSpot]] |publisher=[[CBS Interactive]] |date=17 November 2014 |accessdate=23 November 2014 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6UITcWcb5?url=http://www.gamespot.com/reviews/grand-theft-auto-5-ps4-xbox-one-review/1900-6415959/ |archivedate=23 November 2014 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"garratt1\">{{cite web |url=https://www.vg247.com/2014/08/26/gta-5-gta-online-dlc-1-16-san-andreas-flight-school-missions-nerfed/ |title=GTA Online\u2019s Flight School and patch 1.16 leveled the game \u2013 and it\u2019s for the best |last=Garratt |first=Patrick |work=[[VG247]] |publisher=[[Gamer Network]] |date=26 August 2014 |accessdate=29 March 2016 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6gMAOHk1x?url=https://www.vg247.com/2014/08/26/gta-5-gta-online-dlc-1-16-san-andreas-flight-school-missions-nerfed/ |archivedate=28 March 2016 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nCritical reception of ''GTA Online'' has improved over time. The ''San Andreas Flight School'' update created incentives for players to try the previously neglected aircraft missions and take advantage of the game's \"sensational\" flight modelling, while also more fairly balancing mission payouts relative to their difficulty.<ref name=\"garratt1\"/> The Heists update was also well-received: Liam Martin of [[Digital Spy]] wrote that the update \"strike[s] a great balance between the team and the individual\", praising the update for encouraging \"pinpoint coordination\",<ref name=\"martin1\"/> while IGN's Ryan McCaffrey applauded the replayability and unpredictability.<ref name=\"mccaffrey2\"/> ''Eurogamer's'' Rich Stanton praised the four-player Heists for testing co-ordination as a group by \"forcing players to adopt different starting positions\" which \"add[s] a layer of strategy that wasn't there before\" which is important since the death of one player often forces the team to restart, which was lacking in the Contact Missions. There has been some criticism of the Heists for poorly-placed or absent mission checkpoints, the unnecessary long drives at the start of missions, and frequent technical issues that caused long waiting periods and mid-mission server disconnections.<ref name=\"eurogamer1\"/>\n\n=== Awards ===\n{{Main|List of accolades received by Grand Theft Auto V}}\n\n''Grand Theft Auto Online'' won Best Multiplayer at the [[10th British Academy Games Awards]]<ref name=\"bafta\"/> and from [[GameTrailers]].<ref name=\"GameTrailers\"/> [[Game Revolution]] and ''Hardcore Gamer'' nominated it for Biggest Disappointment.<ref name=\"GR-Disappoint\"/><ref name=\"HG-Disappoint\"/> At the 2019 [[Golden Joystick Awards]], the game was nominated for Still Playing<ref name=\"Golden Joystick 19 Nom\"/> and won Best Game Expansion for ''The Diamond Casino & Resort''.<ref name=\"Golden Joystick 19\"/>\n\n== Notes ==\n{{Notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n<!-- Additional content -->\n<ref name=\"7th Gen\">{{cite web |url=http://metro.co.uk/2015/09/11/no-more-gta-online-updates-for-xbox-360-and-ps3-says-rockstar-5386537/ |title=No more GTA Online updates for Xbox 360 and PS3 says Rockstar |work=[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]] |publisher=[[Daily Mail and General Trust]] |date=11 September 2015 |accessdate=10 February 2016}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"After Hours\">{{cite web |url=https://www.polygon.com/2018/7/19/17588206/gta-online-after-hours-release-date-trailer-gay-tony |title=GTA Online update brings back 'Gay Tony,' lets you run a nightclub |last=McWhertor |first=Michael |work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |publisher=[[Vox Media]] |date=19 July 2018 |accessdate=20 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"anticipated\">{{cite web |url=http://www.redbull.com/en/games/stories/1331710800070/gta-online-heists-hints-and-tips |title=GTA Online: Handy hints for dominating Heists |first=Jon |last=Partridge |date=13 March 2015 |publisher=Red Bull |accessdate=14 March 2015}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Beach Bum\">{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2013/nov/13/gta-online-beach-bum-update-release-date |title=GTA Online: release date announced for Beach Bum update |author=Keith Stuart |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |date=14 November 2013 |accessdate=21 June 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131114015527/http://www.theguardian.com/technology/2013/nov/13/gta-online-beach-bum-update-release-date |archivedate=14 November 2013 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Bikers\">{{cite web |url=http://www.inquisitr.com/3563430/take-a-look-at-all-of-the-new-online-missions-that-were-added-to-gta-v-with-the-bikers-dlc-update/ |title=Take A Look At All Of The New Online Missions That Were Added To \u2018GTA V\u2019 With The Bikers DLC Update |last=Stonecipher |