\n|-\n|20\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|20\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|MEX}} Ignacio Castaneda\n|TKO\n|3 (10)\n|Oct 18, 1970\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|PAN}} {{small|Gimnasio Nuevo Panam\u00e1, Panama City, Panama}}\n|\n|-\n|19\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|19\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|CRI}} Marvin Castaneda\n|KO\n|1 (10), {{small|1:30}}\n|Sep 5, 1970\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|PAN}} {{small|Gimnasio Municipal, [[Puerto Armuelles]], Panama}}\n|\n|-\n|18\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|18\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|MEX}} Clemente Mucino\n|KO\n|6 (10), {{small|2:18}}\n|Jul 18, 1970\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|PAN}} {{small|Arena de Col\u00f3n, Col\u00f3n, Panama}}\n|\n|-\n|17\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|17\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|PAN}} [[Ernesto Marcel]]\n|TKO\n|10 (10)\n|May 16, 1970\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|PAN}} {{small|[[Gimnasio Nuevo Panama]], Panama City, Panama}}\n|\n|-\n|16\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|16\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|MEX}} Felipe Torres\n|UD\n|10\n|Mar 28, 1970\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|MEX}} {{small|[[Mexico City]], Mexico}}\n|\n|-\n|15\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|15\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|PAN}} Luis Patino\n|KO\n|8 (10)\n|Nov 23, 1969\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|PAN}} {{small|Gimnasio Neco de la Guardia, Panama City, Panama}}\n|\n|-\n|14\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|14\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|PAN}} Serafin Garcia\n|TKO\n|5 (8)\n|Sep 21, 1969\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|PAN}} {{small|Gimnasio Neco de la Guardia, Panama City, Panama}}\n|\n|-\n|13\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|13\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|PAN}} Adolfo Osses\n|TKO\n|7 (8)\n|Jun 22, 1969\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|PAN}} {{small|Gimnasio Neco de la Guardia, Panama City, Panama}}\n|\n|-\n|12\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|12\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|PAN}} Jacinto Garcia\n|TKO\n|4 (8)\n|May 18, 1969\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|PAN}} {{small|Gimnasio Neco de la Guardia, Panama City, Panama}}\n|\n|-\n|11\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|11\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|PAN}} Eduardo Frutos\n|UD\n|6\n|Feb 1, 1969\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|PAN}} {{small|[[Estadio Nacional de Panam\u00e1|Estadio Nacional]], Panama City, Panama}}\n|\n|-\n|10\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|10\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|PAN}} Alberto Brand\n|TKO\n|4 (6), {{small|2:50}}\n|Jan 19, 1969\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|PAN}} {{small|Gimnasio Neco de la Guardia, Panama City, Panama}}\n|\n|-\n|9\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|9\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|PAN}} Carlos Howard\n|{{abbr|TKO|Technical knockout}}\n|1 (6)\n|Dec 7, 1968\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|PAN}} {{small|Gimnasio Neco de la Guardia, Panama City, Panama}}\n|\n|-\n|8\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|8\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|PAN}} Juan Gondola\n|KO\n|2 (6)\n|Nov 16, 1968\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|PAN}} {{small|Arena de Col\u00f3n, Col\u00f3n, Panama}}\n|\n|-\n|7\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|7\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|PAN}} Cesar De Leon\n|KO\n|1 (6), {{small|1:20}}\n|Sep 22, 1968\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|PAN}} {{small|Gimnasio Neco de la Guardia, Panama City, Panama}}\n|\n|-\n|6\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|6\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|PAN}} Leroy Carghill\n|KO\n|1 (6)\n|Aug 25, 1968\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|PAN}} {{small|Gimnasio Neco de la Guardia, Panama City, Panama}}\n|\n|-\n|5\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|5\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|PAN}} Enrique Jacobo\n|KO\n|1 (6)\n|Aug 10, 1968\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|PAN}} {{small|Panama City, Panama}}\n|\n|-\n|4\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|4\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|PAN}} Eduardo Morales\n|KO\n|1 (4), {{small|3:00}}\n|Jun 30, 1968\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|PAN}} {{small|Gimnasio Neco de la Guardia, [[Panama City]], Panama}}\n|\n|-\n|3\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|3\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|PAN}} Manuel Jimenez\n|KO\n|1 (4)\n|Jun 15, 1968\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|PAN}} {{small|Arena de Col\u00f3n, Col\u00f3n, Panama}}\n|\n|-\n|2\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|2\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|PAN}} Juan Gondola\n|{{abbr|KO|Knockout}}\n|1 (4)\n|May 14, 1968\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|PAN}} {{small|Col\u00f3n, Panama}}\n|\n|-\n|1\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|1\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|PAN}} Carlos Mendoza\n|{{abbr|UD|Unanimous decision}}\n|4\n|Feb 23, 1968\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|PAN}} {{small|Arena de Col\u00f3n, [[Col\u00f3n, Panama|Col\u00f3n]], Panama}}\n|\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n*[[List of undisputed boxing champions]]\n*[[List of boxing families]]\n*[[List of boxing quadruple champions]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n{{Commons category|Roberto Duran|Roberto Dur\u00e1n}}\n*{{Boxrec|id=000080}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20030219055106/http://www.cmgww.com/sports/duran/ Official website], hosted by CMG Worldwide as Dur\u00e1n's representative\n*[http://www.ibhof.com/pages/about/inductees/modern/duran.html Roberto Dur\u00e1n biography] at the [[International Boxing Hall of Fame]]\n\n{{s-start-collapsible|header={{s-sports}} }}\n{{s-text|style=background:#C1D8FF; font-weight: bold;|text=World boxing titles}}\n{{s-bef|rows=3|before=[[Ken Buchanan]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of WBA world champions#Lightweight|WBA lightweight champion]]\n|years=June 26, 1972 \u2013 January 1979<br>Vacated}}\n{{s-vac|next=[[Ernesto Espa\u00f1a]]}}\n{{s-break}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of The Ring world champions#Lightweight|''The Ring'' lightweight champion]]\n|years=June 26, 1972 \u2013 January 1979<br>Vacated}}\n{{s-vac|next=[[Jim Watt (boxer)|Jim Watt]]}}\n{{s-break}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Lineal lightweight champion\n|years=June 26, 1972 \u2013 January 1979<br>Vacated}}\n{{s-vac|next=[[Alexis Arg\u00fcello]]}}\n{